Trax - Advanced Activity Tracker

A comprehensive, color-coded tracking system for genesis MUD that monitors everything from loot and kills to movement and XP gain!

Features - 

    Tracks: Herbs picked, monster kills, imbues looted, coins collected, rooms moved, bank balance, mortal level progress, ability cooldowns, and more
    Live Updates: Real-time tracking with popup window or tab display or both if you're a madman!
    Mobile Friendly: Type <trax all> for normal text window display on mobile devices, or use the popup window, as it should work on most phones too!
    Persistent Storage: Local save/restore functionality - backs up userdata to keep from corruption
    Customizable Colors: Multiple color presets or create your own
    Easy installation and data management: functions to help you instate your data if you have other trackers!

Components -

    2 Triggers - One tracks room movement and one everything else!

    1 Alias - Main command & control center (trax)

Quick Start -
    Copy all triggers and the alias into your client(or install the package using the package manager)
   
    Type trax init to initialize data storage

    Type trax help for all available commands

    Note: Be sure you're putting everything in right, you need to be careful copy pasting everything, but no coding experience is needed—just copy and paste!

Integration with Hunting/Herbing Scripts -

Trax includes built-in support for Exosphere's hunting/herbing scripts. To enable progress tracking, drop these bits into the right part of both the triggers and aliases of the hunting and herbing script!:

Hunting Script:

gwc.userdata.trax.huntonoff = "on";   // Add to enable section
gwc.userdata.trax.huntonoff = "off";  // Add to disable section
gwc.userdata.trax.huntpaused = true;  // Add to pause section
gwc.userdata.trax.huntpaused = false; // Add to resume section

Herbing Script:

gwc.userdata.trax.herbonoff = "on";   // Add to start new path
gwc.userdata.trax.herbonoff = "off";  // Add to finish path section

Auto-Heal Script:

gwc.userdata.healing = "on";  // Add to enable and end sections

The script works perfectly without these—they're optional enhancements!

